query.result:
133 All look at him, all honor him: 134 there I saw Socrates and Plato, 135 who before the others stand nearer to them;
136 Democritus who the world at random places, 137 Diogenes, Anaxagoras and such, 138 Empedocles, Heraclitus and Zeno;
139 and I saw the good host of whom, 140 I say Diacrodus; and I saw Orpheus, 141 Tullio and Lino and moral Seneca;
142 Euclid geometer and Ptolemy, 143 Hippocrates, Avicenna and Galen, 144 Averroes, who the great commentary made.
